data.title: Jessica DiCicco
authors: Contributors to The Loud House Encyclopedia
data.text:
Jessica Sonya DiCicco is an American actress and voice artist. She provides the voices of Lynn, Lucy, and Zach, reprising her role as Lucy in Nickelodeon All-Star Brawl.[1] She also voiced Benny Stein and the unnamed teen girl in season 2 only. She also became the narrator of the Nick Jr. Channel after Moose and Zee were removed in March 2012, when the channel rebranded in May 2018 and September 2023 she remained on the channel.

Trivia[]

She is married to Josh Lewis and they have two children.

Their first child was born after DiCicco recorded a Loud House episode in 2018, thus causing her voice for Lynn to sound a bit lower in "Middle Men".

Her voice for Lynn Jr. has gradually gotten deeper, raspier, and more boyish-sounding in Season 3.

When Moose and Zee were removed from Nick Jr. on March 1, 2012, Jessica took over for the channel, although some segments that had Moose's voice from the puzzle time segments were moved to the word play and count it up segments, despite the segments being the same segments, they audio was remade with Jessica narrating them instead of Paul Christie (Moose A. Moose's voice actor), however the kids voices answering remained intact until 2015.

This occurred with some of the Puzzle Time segments such as R Finding, B Finding, E Finding, At Rhyming, Og Rhyming, Ock Rhyming, and Octagon Finding, though some segments that didn't include Moose and Zee (Such as clips from Story Time, Zee's Garden, My Neighborhood, And Black History Month) were still airing after Moose and Zee left, however she didn't narrate those.
